The paper discusses the modified SNIP indicator of Elsevier, which is a bibliometric measure used in the field of computer science to evaluate the impact of scientific journals. The paper also mentions the problems with the original SNIP indicator, which is commonly used in the field of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CY (Computational Geometry), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
